        <div style="text-align: center;">
            <span style="font-family: 'INK Free', cursive;">
                <h1>Minimalist Style</h1>
            </span>
        </div>
        <div style="text-align: center;">
            <h4><em>    ‘Minimalist interior design is about simplicity, functionality, and creating a sense of calm and order. It embraces the idea of "less is more" 
                and creates a serene and uncluttered space.’ </em></h4>
        </div>
        <div style="text-align: justify;">
            <p>Minimalist interior design is very similar to modern interior design and involves using the bare essentials to create a 
                simple and uncluttered space. It’s characterised by simplicity, clean lines, and a monochromatic palette with colour used 
                as an accent. It usually combines an open floor plan, lots of light, and functional furniture, and it focuses on the shape, 
                colour and texture of just a handful of essential elements. </p>
        </div><br>
        <h1><span style="color: rgb(15, 4, 25);">1.Living Room</span></h1>
        <div style="text-align: center;">
            <img src="mliving room 01.jpg" alt="Living Room" width="500">
            <img src="mliving room 02.jpeg" alt="Living Room" width="500" height="320">
        </div><br>
        <div style="color: #453F3F;">
            <p>The minimalist living room aims to create a tranquil and uncluttered space for relaxation and socializing. Start by 
                selecting a neutral color palette, such as whites, grays, or earth tones, to establish a calm atmosphere. Choose 
                furniture with sleek and clean lines, avoiding ornate details. Opt for a comfortable sofa, a minimalist coffee table, 
                and a few well-chosen accent chairs. Keep the number of decorative items to a minimum, and focus on incorporating a few 
                statement pieces that add visual interest without overwhelming the space. Use storage solutions such as built-in cabinets 
                or hidden storage to maintain a clutter-free environment. </p>
        </div>
        <h1><span style="color: rgb(15, 4, 25);">2. Master Bedroom</span></h1>
        <div style="text-align: center;">
            <img src="mmaster bedroom 01.jpg" alt="Master Bedtoom" width="500" height="370">
            <img src="mmaster bedroom 02.jpg" alt="Master Bedtoom" width="500" >
        </div>
        <div style="color: #453F3F;">
            <p>In a minimalist master bedroom, simplicity and serenity are key. Select a neutral color scheme to create a soothing 
                atmosphere. Choose a platform bed with a minimalist frame and simple bedding. Keep the nightstands clean and uncluttered, 
                with just a few essential items. Use built-in or minimalistic wardrobes to maintain a streamlined appearance. Consider 
                incorporating natural materials such as wood or bamboo for furniture and flooring to add warmth and texture to the space. 
                Use soft and indirect lighting to create a relaxing ambiance. </p>
        </div><br>
        <h1><span style="color: rgb(15, 4, 25);">3. Children Room</span></h1>
        <div style="text-align: center;">
            <img src="mkidroom 01.jpg" alt="Children Room" width="500">
            <img src="mkidroom 02.jpg" alt="Children Room" width="500" height="350">
        </div>
        <div style="color: #453F3F;">
            <p>In a minimalist children's room, the focus is on creating a calm and organized space. Opt for a neutral color palette with 
                pops of color for accents. Use multi-functional furniture pieces, such as beds with built-in storage or desks that can 
                double as play areas. Keep toys and belongings organized with minimalist storage solutions, such as floating shelves or 
                under-bed storage. Limit the number of decorative elements and encourage a clean and clutter-free environment. </p>
        </div>
        <h1><span style="color: rgb(15, 4, 25);">4. Bathroom</span></h1>
        <div style="text-align: center;">
            <img src="mbathroom 01.jpg" alt="Bathroom" width="500">
            <img src="mbathroom 02.jpg" alt="Bathroom" width="500" height="350">
        </div>
        <div style="color: #453F3F;">
            <p>Minimalist style can be applied to the toilet by embracing simplicity and functionality. Choose clean and simple fixtures 
                and fittings with sleek lines. Use a neutral color palette for walls and floors, such as white or light gray. Incorporate 
                storage solutions that keep toiletries and cleaning supplies hidden, maintaining a clutter-free look. Opt for 
                minimalistic accessories and keep the space well-ventilated and well-lit. </p>
        </div>
        <h1><span style="color: rgb(15, 4, 25);">5. Kitchen</span></h1>
        <div style="text-align: center;">
            <img src="mkitchen 01.jpg" alt="Kitchen" width="500" height="350">
            <img src="mkitchen 02.jpeg" alt="Kitchen" width="500">
        </div>
        <div style="color: #453F3F;">
            <p>In a minimalist kitchen, clean lines and a clutter-free environment are essential. Opt for sleek and simple cabinets with 
                hidden handles for a seamless appearance. Choose neutral colors for the cabinetry and countertops, and use a backsplash 
                with a minimalist design. Keep countertops clear of unnecessary items, and utilize built-in storage solutions to maintain 
                a clutter-free space. Use pendant lights or recessed lighting to create a bright and inviting atmosphere. </p>
        </div>
